Text: Menstruation is just a technical way to say period. It’s that time of a month when a woman bleeds for a few days as her body sheds the extra lining her uterus builds up to support pregnancy. If there’s no baby, you’ll get your period. Every month 🙃.

Text: Gonorrhea  (aka “the clap” or "the drip") is an STD that is passed along through sex. That means ALL kinds of sex including anal and oral (so yes, you get it while giving head). Signs of gonorrhea are burning while peeing, bleeding between periods, or yellowish/bloody discharge 😬.
